 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-8: Background F(S) warmup — eliminate 30s cold start on first status after daemon start (INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: Even with the daemon, the first braid status after startup pays ~30s for compute_fitness (cold computation). All subsequent calls are <1s (cached). This 30s cold start degrades the first-command experience. APPROACH: (1) On daemon startup, after loading the store, spawn a background task that computes F(S) and coherence immediately. Use tokio::task::spawn_blocking since compute_fitness is CPU-bound and blocks the async runtime. (2) Store the result in an Arc<Mutex<Option<FitnessScore>>>. (3) When a command requests fitness: if Some, return immediately. If None (still computing), either block-wait or serve a stale cache from fitness.json. (4) Progressive warmup: compute cheap components first (uncertainty, harvest_quality) then expensive ones (drift, contradiction). Serve partial results if available. (5) Alternative: on daemon start, check fitness.json. If it exists and is recent (<1h old), serve it immediately while recomputing in background. This gives instant-but-stale followed by fresh. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Second braid status < 1s regardless of daemon restart. (B) First braid status < 2s if fitness.json exists from previous session. (C) First braid status shows accurate F(S) (eventual consistency — may be stale for <30s). (D) Background computation does not block other daemon commands. DEPENDS-ON: DAEMON-4 (lazy F(S) cache). FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-019."
